<h2 id="section-top">Diabetic Medicine</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=29674">Derbyshire Community Health Services NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent3833ea5c1128437fbf749ff2e37b750a">
</div>
<p>The Community Diabetes Specialist Nursing Team provides a service for people with Type 1 and Type 2 diabetes living in North Derbyshire. </p>
<p>Our specialist nurses support people to improve overall diabetes management and to reduce short and long term complications.</p>
<p>The team will;</p>
<ul>
<li>alter treatment programmes</li>
<li>initiate new treatments  </li>
<li>advise and counsel people on how to manage and live with their diabetes more effectively</li>
<li>provide support and advice and  training for health care professionals working in the community.</li>
<li>write individual diabetes care plan</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><br/></strong></p>
<p><strong>Accessing the service</strong></p>
<p>Referrals can be made by any health professional, professions allied to health or by individuals living with diabetes, your GP will be contacted.</p>
<p>Patients will be seen either in a clinic setting local to them, or via a home visit for diabetes management plans </p>
<p><br/><strong>Service locations</strong></p>
<p>Clinics are held in the locations indicated opposite.<br/><br/><br/><strong>Educational programmes</strong></p>
<p>We provide and support a number of educational programmes on diabetes management for people living with diabetes. </p>
<p>The team is also available as a resource to other practitioners and staff caring for people with diabetes, offering advice, support and teaching either via the telephone or face to face.</p>
<p><br/><strong>Contact:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Telephone: 01629 817878</strong></p>
<p>North Derbyshire:<br/>Michelle Denyer (Lead Community diabetes nurse)</p>
<p><a href="mailto:michelle.denyer@nhs.net">michelle.denyer@nhs.net</a></p>
<p> Diabetes specialist nurses</p>
<p>Beth Cooper</p>
<p>Joanne Hulme</p>
<p>Clare Reynolds<br/><br/><br/>For further information or to make a referral contact the Specialist Diabetes Team<br/><br/><strong>Postal address</strong><br/>Community diabetes nurses<br/>Newholme Hospital<br/>Baslow Road<br/>Bakewell<br/>Derbyshire<br/>DE45 1AD<br/>Fax: 01629817890</p>
<p><br/><strong>Satellite address</strong><br/>Cavendish Hospital<br/>Manchester Road<br/>Buxton<br/>SK17 6TE</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Useful links</strong></p>
<p>Further information about diabetes and support groups leading diabetes charity Diabetes UK.<br/><a href="http://www.diabetes.org.uk" target="_blank">www.diabetes.org.uk</a></p>
<p><br/>NHS Diabetes works to raise the quality of diabetes care in England by supporting and working with the healthcare community and people with diabetes.<br/><a href="http://www.diabetes.nhs.uk" target="_blank">www.diabetes.nhs.uk</a></p></div>
